import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Define the features and target variable
X = data_df[['x']]
y = data_df['y']

# Create and fit the model
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X, y)

# Get the slope (coefficient) and y-intercept
slope = model.coef_[0]
intercept = model.intercept_

# Predict y values using the model
y_pred = model.predict(X)

# Calculate the coefficient of correlation (R)
correlation_coefficient = np.corrcoef(data_df['x'], data_df['y'])[0, 1]

# Plotting the data points and the regression line
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.scatter(data_df['x'], data_df['y'], color='blue', label='Data Points')
plt.plot(data_df['x'], y_pred, color='red', label='Regression Line')
plt.title('Linear Regression Example')
plt.xlabel('x')
plt.ylabel('y')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()
plt.show()
